91class DeclareStructTypesTraverser : public TIntermTraverser
92{
93 public:
94 explicit DeclareStructTypesTraverser(TOutputMSL *outputMSL)
95 : TIntermTraverser(true, false, false), mOutputMSL(outputMSL)
96 {}
97
98 bool visitDeclaration(Visit visit, TIntermDeclaration *node) override
99 {
100 ASSERT(visit == PreVisit);
101 if (!mInGlobalScope)
102 {
103 return false;
104 }
105
106 const TIntermSequence &sequence = *(node->getSequence());
107 TIntermTyped *declarator = sequence.front()->getAsTyped();
108 const TType &type = declarator->getType();
109
110 if (type.isStructSpecifier())
111 {
112 const TStructure *structure = type.getStruct();
113
114 // Embedded structs should be parsed away by now.
115 ASSERT(structure->symbolType() != SymbolType::Empty);
116 // outputMSL->writeStructType(structure);
117
118 TIntermSymbol *symbolNode = declarator->getAsSymbolNode();
119 if (symbolNode && symbolNode->variable().symbolType() == SymbolType::Empty)
120 {
121 // Remove the struct specifier declaration from the tree so it isn't parsed again.
122 TIntermSequence emptyReplacement;
123 mMultiReplacements.emplace_back(getParentNode()->getAsBlock(), node,
124 emptyReplacement);
125 }
126 }
127 // TODO: REMOVE, used to remove 'unsued' warning
128 mOutputMSL = nullptr;
129
130 return false;
131 }
132
133 private:
134 TOutputMSL *mOutputMSL;
135};
136
137class DeclareDefaultUniformsTraverser : public TIntermTraverser
138{
139 public:
140 DeclareDefaultUniformsTraverser(TInfoSinkBase *sink,
141 ShHashFunction64 hashFunction,
142 NameMap *nameMap)
143 : TIntermTraverser(true, true, true),
144 mSink(sink),
145 mHashFunction(hashFunction),
146 mNameMap(nameMap),
147 mInDefaultUniform(false)
148 {}
149
150 bool visitDeclaration(Visit visit, TIntermDeclaration *node) override
151 {
152 const TIntermSequence &sequence = *(node->getSequence());
153
154 // TODO(jmadill): Compound declarations.
155 ASSERT(sequence.size() == 1);
156
157 TIntermTyped *variable = sequence.front()->getAsTyped();
158 const TType &type = variable->getType();
159 bool isUniform = type.getQualifier() == EvqUniform && !type.isInterfaceBlock() &&
160 !IsOpaqueType(type.getBasicType());
161
162 if (visit == PreVisit)
163 {
164 if (isUniform)
165 {
166 (*mSink) << " " << GetTypeName(type, mHashFunction, mNameMap) << " ";
167 mInDefaultUniform = true;
168 }
169 }
170 else if (visit == InVisit)
171 {
172 mInDefaultUniform = isUniform;
173 }
174 else if (visit == PostVisit)
175 {
176 if (isUniform)
177 {
178 (*mSink) << ";\n";
179
180 // Remove the uniform declaration from the tree so it isn't parsed again.
181 TIntermSequence emptyReplacement;
182 mMultiReplacements.emplace_back(getParentNode()->getAsBlock(), node,
183 emptyReplacement);
184 }
185
186 mInDefaultUniform = false;
187 }
188 return true;
189 }
190
191 void visitSymbol(TIntermSymbol *symbol) override
192 {
193 if (mInDefaultUniform)
194 {
195 const ImmutableString &name = symbol->variable().name();
196 ASSERT(!name.beginsWith("gl_"));
197 (*mSink) << HashName(&symbol->variable(), mHashFunction, mNameMap)
198 << ArrayString(symbol->getType());
199 }
200 }
201
202 private:
203 TInfoSinkBase *mSink;
204 ShHashFunction64 mHashFunction;
205 NameMap *mNameMap;
206 bool mInDefaultUniform;
207};

209TIntermBinary *CreateDriverUniformRef(const TVariable &driverUniforms, const char *fieldName)
210{
211 size_t fieldIndex = FindFieldIndex(driverUniforms.getType().getStruct()->fields(), fieldName);
212
213 TIntermSymbol *angleUniformsRef = new TIntermSymbol(&driverUniforms);
214 TConstantUnion *uniformIndex = new TConstantUnion;
215 uniformIndex->setIConst(static_cast<int>(fieldIndex));
216 TIntermConstantUnion *indexRef =
217 new TIntermConstantUnion(uniformIndex, *StaticType::GetBasic<EbtInt>());
218 return new TIntermBinary(EOpIndexDirectStruct, angleUniformsRef, indexRef);
219}

221#if 0
222// Unlike Vulkan having auto viewport flipping extension, in Metal we have to flip gl_Position.y
223// manually.
224// This operation performs flipping the gl_Position.y using this expression:
225// gl_Position.y = gl_Position.y * negViewportScaleY
226ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool AppendVertexShaderPositionYCorrectionToMain(TCompiler &compiler,
227 TIntermBlock &root,
228 TIntermSwizzle &negFlipY)
229{
230 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = compiler.getSymbolTable();
231
232 // Create a symbol reference to "gl_Position"
233 const TVariable *position = BuiltInVariable::gl_Position();
234 TIntermSymbol *positionRef = new TIntermSymbol(position);
235
236 // Create a swizzle to "gl_Position.y"
237 TVector<int> swizzleOffsetY;
238 swizzleOffsetY.push_back(1);
239 TIntermSwizzle *positionY = new TIntermSwizzle(positionRef, swizzleOffsetY);
240
241 // Create the expression "gl_Position.y * negFlipY"
242 TIntermBinary *inverseY = new TIntermBinary(EOpMul, positionY->deepCopy(), &negFlipY);
243
244 // Create the assignment "gl_Position.y = gl_Position.y * negViewportScaleY
245 TIntermTyped *positionYLHS = positionY->deepCopy();
246 TIntermBinary *assignment = new TIntermBinary(TOperator::EOpAssign, positionYLHS, inverseY);
247
248 // Append the assignment as a statement at the end of the shader.
249 return RunAtTheEndOfShader(&compiler, &root, assignment, &symbolTable);
250}
251#endif

253#if 0
254// Initialize unused varying outputs.
255ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool InitializeUnusedOutputs(TIntermBlock &root,
256 TSymbolTable &symbolTable,
257 const InitVariableList &unusedVars)
258{
259 if (unusedVars.empty())
260 {
261 return true;
262 }
263
264 TIntermSequence *insertSequence = new TIntermSequence;
265
266 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &var : unusedVars)
267 {
268 ASSERT(!var.active);
269 const TIntermSymbol *symbol = FindSymbolNode(&root, var.name);
270 ASSERT(symbol);
271
272 TIntermSequence *initCode = CreateInitCode(symbol, false, false, &symbolTable);
273
274 insertSequence->insert(insertSequence->end(), initCode->begin(), initCode->end());
275 }
276
277 if (insertSequence)
278 {
279 TIntermFunctionDefinition *main = FindMain(&root);
280 TIntermSequence *mainSequence = main->getBody()->getSequence();
281
282 // Insert init code at the start of main()
283 mainSequence->insert(mainSequence->begin(), insertSequence->begin(), insertSequence->end());
284 }
285
286 return true;
287}

290const TVariable *AddComputeDriverUniformsToShader(TIntermBlock &root, TSymbolTable &symbolTable)
291{
292 // This field list mirrors the structure of ComputeDriverUniforms in ContextVk.cpp.
293 TFieldList *driverFieldList = new TFieldList;
294
295 const std::array<TType *, kNumComputeDriverUniforms> kDriverUniformTypes = {{
296 new TType(EbtUInt, 4),
297 }};
298
299 for (size_t uniformIndex = 0; uniformIndex < kNumComputeDriverUniforms; ++uniformIndex)
300 {
301 TField *driverUniformField =
302 new TField(kDriverUniformTypes[uniformIndex],
303 ImmutableString(kComputeDriverUniformNames[uniformIndex]), kNoSourceLoc,
304 SymbolType::AngleInternal);
305 driverFieldList->push_back(driverUniformField);
306 }
307
308 return DeclareStructure(&root, &symbolTable, driverFieldList, EvqUniform,
309 TMemoryQualifier::Create(), 0, kUniformsBlockName.rawName(),
310 &kUniformsVarName.rawName())
311 .second;
312}
313
314// The Add*DriverUniformsToShader operation adds an internal uniform block to a shader. The driver
315// block is used to implement Vulkan-specific features and workarounds. Returns the driver uniforms
316// variable.
317//
318// There are Graphics and Compute variations as they require different uniforms.
319const TVariable *AddGraphicsDriverUniformsToShader(TIntermBlock &root,
320 TSymbolTable &symbolTable,
321 const std::vector<TField *> &additionalFields)
322{
323 // Init the depth range type.
324 TFieldList *depthRangeParamsFields = new TFieldList();
325 depthRangeParamsFields->push_back(new TField(new TType(EbtFloat, EbpHigh, EvqGlobal, 1, 1),
326 ImmutableString("near"), kNoSourceLoc,
327 SymbolType::AngleInternal));
328 depthRangeParamsFields->push_back(new TField(new TType(EbtFloat, EbpHigh, EvqGlobal, 1, 1),
329 ImmutableString("far"), kNoSourceLoc,
330 SymbolType::AngleInternal));
331 depthRangeParamsFields->push_back(new TField(new TType(EbtFloat, EbpHigh, EvqGlobal, 1, 1),
332 ImmutableString("diff"), kNoSourceLoc,
333 SymbolType::AngleInternal));
334 // This additional field might be used by subclass such as TranslatorMetal.
335 depthRangeParamsFields->push_back(new TField(new TType(EbtFloat, EbpHigh, EvqGlobal, 1, 1),
336 ImmutableString("reserved"), kNoSourceLoc,
337 SymbolType::AngleInternal));
338
339 const TStructure *emulatedDepthRangeParams =
340 DeclareStructure(&root, &symbolTable, depthRangeParamsFields, EvqGlobal,
341 TMemoryQualifier::Create(), 0, kEmulatedDepthRangeParams.rawName(),
342 nullptr)
343 .first->getType()
344 .getStruct();
345
346 // This field list mirrors the structure of GraphicsDriverUniforms in ContextMtl.cpp.
347 TFieldList *driverFieldList = new TFieldList;
348
349 const std::array<TType *, kNumGraphicsDriverUniforms> kDriverUniformTypes = {{
350 new TType(EbtFloat, 4),
351 new TType(EbtFloat, 2),
352 new TType(EbtFloat, 2),
353 new TType(EbtFloat, 2),
354 new TType(EbtUInt), // uint clipDistancesEnabled; // 32 bits for 32 clip distances max
355 new TType(EbtUInt),
356 new TType(EbtUInt),
357 // NOTE: There's a vec3 gap here that can be used in the future
358 new TType(EbtInt, 4),
359 new TType(EbtUInt, 4),
360 new TType(emulatedDepthRangeParams, false),
361 }};
362
363 for (size_t uniformIndex = 0; uniformIndex < kNumGraphicsDriverUniforms; ++uniformIndex)
364 {
365 TField *driverUniformField =
366 new TField(kDriverUniformTypes[uniformIndex],
367 ImmutableString(kGraphicsDriverUniformNames[uniformIndex]), kNoSourceLoc,
368 SymbolType::AngleInternal);
369 driverFieldList->push_back(driverUniformField);
370 }
371
372 // Back-end specific fields
373 driverFieldList->insert(driverFieldList->end(), additionalFields.begin(),
374 additionalFields.end());
375
376 // Define a driver uniform block "ANGLEUniformBlock" with instance name "ANGLEUniforms".
377 return DeclareStructure(&root, &symbolTable, driverFieldList, EvqUniform,
378 TMemoryQualifier::Create(), 0, kUniformsBlockName.rawName(),
379 &kUniformsVarName.rawName())
380 .second;
381}

383// Declares a new variable to replace gl_DepthRange, its values are fed from a driver uniform.
384ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool ReplaceGLDepthRangeWithDriverUniform(TCompiler &compiler,
385 TIntermBlock &root,
386 const TVariable &driverUniforms)
387{
388 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = compiler.getSymbolTable();
389
390 // Create a symbol reference to "gl_DepthRange"
391 const TVariable *depthRangeVar = static_cast<const TVariable *>(
392 symbolTable.findBuiltIn(ImmutableString("gl_DepthRange"), 0));
393
394 // ANGLEUniforms.depthRange
395 TIntermBinary *angleEmulatedDepthRangeRef = CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kDepthRange);
396
397 // Use this variable instead of gl_DepthRange everywhere.
398 return ReplaceVariableWithTyped(&compiler, &root, depthRangeVar, angleEmulatedDepthRangeRef);
399}

407ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool AppendVertexShaderTransformFeedbackOutputToMain(TCompiler &compiler,
408 SymbolEnv &mSymbolEnv,
409 TIntermBlock &root)
410{
411 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = compiler.getSymbolTable();

417// This operation performs the viewport depth translation needed by Vulkan. In GL the viewport
418// transformation is slightly different - see the GL 2.0 spec section "2.12.1 Controlling the
419// Viewport". In Vulkan the corresponding spec section is currently "23.4. Coordinate
420// Transformations".
421// The equations reduce to an expression:
422//
423// z_vk = 0.5 * (w_gl + z_gl)
424//
425// where z_vk is the depth output of a Vulkan vertex shader and z_gl is the same for GL.
426ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool AppendVertexShaderDepthCorrectionToMain(TCompiler &compiler,
427 TIntermBlock &root)
428{
429 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = compiler.getSymbolTable();
430
431 const TVariable *position = BuiltInVariable::gl_Position();
432 TIntermSymbol *positionRef = new TIntermSymbol(position);
433
434 TVector<int> swizzleOffsetZ = {2};
435 TIntermSwizzle *positionZ = new TIntermSwizzle(positionRef, swizzleOffsetZ);
436
437 TIntermConstantUnion *oneHalf = CreateFloatNode(0.5f);
438
439 TVector<int> swizzleOffsetW = {3};
440 TIntermSwizzle *positionW = new TIntermSwizzle(positionRef->deepCopy(), swizzleOffsetW);
441
442 // Create the expression "(gl_Position.z + gl_Position.w) * 0.5".
443 TIntermBinary *zPlusW = new TIntermBinary(EOpAdd, positionZ->deepCopy(), positionW->deepCopy());
444 TIntermBinary *halfZPlusW = new TIntermBinary(EOpMul, zPlusW, oneHalf->deepCopy());
445
446 // Create the assignment "gl_Position.z = (gl_Position.z + gl_Position.w) * 0.5"
447 TIntermTyped *positionZLHS = positionZ->deepCopy();
448 TIntermBinary *assignment = new TIntermBinary(TOperator::EOpAssign, positionZLHS, halfZPlusW);
449
450 // Append the assignment as a statement at the end of the shader.
451 return RunAtTheEndOfShader(&compiler, &root, assignment, &symbolTable);
452}

454ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool RotateAndFlipBuiltinVariable(TCompiler &compiler,
455 TIntermBlock &root,
456 TIntermSequence &insertSequence,
457 TIntermTyped &flipXY,
458 const TVariable &builtin,
459 const Name &flippedVariableName,
460 TIntermTyped &pivot,
461 TIntermTyped *fragRotation)
462{
463 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = compiler.getSymbolTable();
464
465 // Create a symbol reference to 'builtin'.
466 TIntermSymbol *builtinRef = new TIntermSymbol(&builtin);
467
468 // Create a swizzle to "builtin.xy"
469 TVector<int> swizzleOffsetXY = {0, 1};
470 TIntermSwizzle *builtinXY = new TIntermSwizzle(builtinRef, swizzleOffsetXY);
471
472 // Create a symbol reference to our new variable that will hold the modified builtin.
473 const TType *type = StaticType::GetForVec<EbtFloat>(
474 EvqGlobal, static_cast<unsigned char>(builtin.getType().getNominalSize()));
475 TVariable *replacementVar = new TVariable(&symbolTable, flippedVariableName.rawName(), type,
476 flippedVariableName.symbolType());
477 DeclareGlobalVariable(&root, replacementVar);
478 TIntermSymbol *flippedBuiltinRef = new TIntermSymbol(replacementVar);
479
480 // Use this new variable instead of 'builtin' everywhere.
481 if (!ReplaceVariable(&compiler, &root, &builtin, replacementVar))
482 {
483 return false;
484 }
485
486 // Create the expression "(builtin.xy * fragRotation)"
487 TIntermTyped *rotatedXY;
488 if (fragRotation)
489 {
490 rotatedXY = new TIntermBinary(EOpMatrixTimesVector, fragRotation->deepCopy(),
491 builtinXY->deepCopy());
492 }
493 else
494 {
495 // No rotation applied, use original variable.
496 rotatedXY = builtinXY->deepCopy();
497 }
498
499 // Create the expression "(builtin.xy - pivot) * flipXY + pivot
500 TIntermBinary *removePivot = new TIntermBinary(EOpSub, rotatedXY, &pivot);
501 TIntermBinary *inverseXY = new TIntermBinary(EOpMul, removePivot, &flipXY);
502 TIntermBinary *plusPivot = new TIntermBinary(EOpAdd, inverseXY, pivot.deepCopy());
503
504 // Create the corrected variable and copy the value of the original builtin.
505 TIntermSequence *sequence = new TIntermSequence();
506 sequence->push_back(builtinRef->deepCopy());
507 TIntermAggregate *aggregate = TIntermAggregate::CreateConstructor(builtin.getType(), sequence);
508 TIntermBinary *assignment = new TIntermBinary(EOpInitialize, flippedBuiltinRef, aggregate);
509
510 // Create an assignment to the replaced variable's .xy.
511 TIntermSwizzle *correctedXY =
512 new TIntermSwizzle(flippedBuiltinRef->deepCopy(), swizzleOffsetXY);
513 TIntermBinary *assignToY = new TIntermBinary(EOpAssign, correctedXY, plusPivot);
514
515 // Add this assigment at the beginning of the main function
516 {
517 TIntermBinary *nodes[] = {assignment, assignToY};
518 insertSequence.insert(insertSequence.begin(), std::begin(nodes), std::end(nodes));
519 }
520
521 return compiler.validateAST(&root);
522}

524ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool InsertFragCoordCorrection(TCompiler &compiler,
525 ShCompileOptions compileOptions,
526 TIntermBlock &root,
527 TIntermSequence &insertSequence,
528 const TVariable &driverUniforms)
529{
530 TIntermBinary &flipXY = *CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kFlipXY);
531 TIntermBinary &pivot = *CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kHalfRenderArea);
532 TIntermBinary *fragRotation = nullptr;
533 return RotateAndFlipBuiltinVariable(compiler, root, insertSequence, flipXY,
534 *BuiltInVariable::gl_FragCoord(), kFlippedFragCoordName,
535 pivot, fragRotation);
536}

582ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool AddFragDataDeclaration(TCompiler &compiler, TIntermBlock &root)
583{
584 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = compiler.getSymbolTable();
585 const int maxDrawBuffers = compiler.getResources().MaxDrawBuffers;
586 TType *gl_FragDataType = new TType(EbtFloat, EbpMedium, EvqFragData, 4, 1);
587 std::vector<const TVariable *> glFragDataSlots;
588 TIntermSequence declareGLFragdataSequence;
589
590 // Create gl_FragData_0,1,2,3
591 for (int i = 0; i < maxDrawBuffers; i++)
592 {
593 ImmutableStringBuilder builder(strlen("gl_FragData_") + 2);
594 builder << "gl_FragData_";
595 builder.appendDecimal(i);
596 const TVariable *glFragData =
597 new TVariable(&symbolTable, builder, gl_FragDataType, SymbolType::AngleInternal,
598 TExtension::UNDEFINED);
599 glFragDataSlots.push_back(glFragData);
600 declareGLFragdataSequence.push_back(new TIntermDeclaration{glFragData});
601 }
602 root.insertChildNodes(FindMainIndex(&root), declareGLFragdataSequence);
603
604 // Create an internal gl_FragData array type, compatible with indexing syntax.
605 TType *gl_FragDataTypeArray = new TType(EbtFloat, EbpMedium, EvqGlobal, 4, 1);
606 gl_FragDataTypeArray->makeArray(maxDrawBuffers);
607 const TVariable *glFragDataGlobal = new TVariable(&symbolTable, ImmutableString("gl_FragData"),
608 gl_FragDataTypeArray, SymbolType::BuiltIn);
609
610 DeclareGlobalVariable(&root, glFragDataGlobal);
611 const TIntermSymbol *originalGLFragData = FindSymbolNode(&root, ImmutableString("gl_FragData"));
612 ASSERT(originalGLFragData);
613
614 // Replace gl_FragData() with our globally defined fragdata
615 if (!ReplaceVariable(&compiler, &root, &(originalGLFragData->variable()), glFragDataGlobal))
616 {
617 return false;
618 }
619
620 // Assign each array attribute to an output
621 TIntermBlock *insertSequence = new TIntermBlock();
622 for (int i = 0; i < maxDrawBuffers; i++)
623 {
624 TIntermTyped *glFragDataSlot = new TIntermSymbol(glFragDataSlots[i]);
625 TIntermTyped *glFragDataGlobalSymbol = new TIntermSymbol(glFragDataGlobal);
626 auto &access = AccessIndex(*glFragDataGlobalSymbol, i);
627 TIntermBinary *assignment =
628 new TIntermBinary(TOperator::EOpAssign, glFragDataSlot, &access);
629 insertSequence->appendStatement(assignment);
630 }
631 return RunAtTheEndOfShader(&compiler, &root, insertSequence, &symbolTable);
632}
633
634ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool EmulateInstanceID(TCompiler &compiler,
635 TIntermBlock &root,
636 const TVariable &driverUniforms)
637{
638 TIntermBinary *emuInstanceID =
639 CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kEmuInstanceIDField.rawName().data());
640 const TVariable *instanceID = BuiltInVariable::gl_InstanceIndex();
641 return ReplaceVariableWithTyped(&compiler, &root, instanceID, emuInstanceID);
642}
643
644// Unlike Vulkan having auto viewport flipping extension, in Metal we have to flip gl_Position.y
645// manually.
646// This operation performs flipping the gl_Position.y using this expression:
647// gl_Position.y = gl_Position.y * negViewportScaleY
648ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool AppendVertexShaderPositionYCorrectionToMain(TCompiler &compiler,
649 TIntermBlock &root,
650 TIntermSwizzle &negFlipY)
651{
652 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = compiler.getSymbolTable();
653
654 const TVariable *position = BuiltInVariable::gl_Position();
655 TIntermSymbol *positionRef = new TIntermSymbol(position);
656
657 TVector<int> swizzleOffsetY;
658 swizzleOffsetY.push_back(1);
659 TIntermSwizzle *positionY = new TIntermSwizzle(positionRef, swizzleOffsetY);
660
661 // Create the expression "gl_Position.y * negFlipY"
662 TIntermBinary *inverseY = new TIntermBinary(EOpMul, positionY->deepCopy(), &negFlipY);
663
664 // Create the assignment "gl_Position.y = gl_Position.y * negViewportScaleY
665 TIntermTyped *positionYLHS = positionY->deepCopy();
666 TIntermBinary *assignment = new TIntermBinary(TOperator::EOpAssign, positionYLHS, inverseY);
667
668 // Append the assignment as a statement at the end of the shader.
669 return RunAtTheEndOfShader(&compiler, &root, assignment, &symbolTable);
670}
671} // namespace

691// Add sample_mask writing to main, guarded by the function constant
692// kCoverageMaskEnabledName
693ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool TranslatorMetalDirect::insertSampleMaskWritingLogic(TIntermBlock &root,
694 const TVariable &driverUniforms)
695{
696 TSymbolTable *symbolTable = &getSymbolTable();
697
698 // Create kCoverageMaskEnabled and kSampleMaskWriteFuncName variable references.
699 TType *boolType = new TType(EbtBool);
700 boolType->setQualifier(EvqConst);
701 TVariable *coverageMaskEnabledVar =
702 new TVariable(symbolTable, constant_names::kCoverageMaskEnabled.rawName(), boolType,
703 SymbolType::AngleInternal);
704
705 TFunction *sampleMaskWriteFunc =
706 new TFunction(symbolTable, kSampleMaskWriteFuncName.rawName(), kSampleMaskWriteFuncName.symbolType(),
707 StaticType::GetBasic<EbtVoid>(), false);
708
709 TType *uintType = new TType(EbtUInt);
710 TVariable *maskArg =
711 new TVariable(symbolTable, ImmutableString("mask"), uintType, SymbolType::AngleInternal);
712 sampleMaskWriteFunc->addParameter(maskArg);
713
714 TVariable *gl_SampleMaskArg =
715 new TVariable(symbolTable, ImmutableString("gl_SampleMask"), uintType, SymbolType::AngleInternal);
716 sampleMaskWriteFunc->addParameter(gl_SampleMaskArg);
717
718 // Insert this code to the end of main()
719 // if (ANGLE_CoverageMaskEnabled)
720 // {
721 // ANGLE_writeSampleMask(ANGLE_angleUniforms.coverageMask, ANGLE_fragmentOut.gl_SampleMask);
722 // }
723 TIntermSequence *args = new TIntermSequence;
724 TIntermBinary *coverageMask = CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kCoverageMaskField.rawName().data());
725 args->push_back(coverageMask);
726 const TIntermSymbol *gl_SampleMask = FindSymbolNode(&root, ImmutableString("gl_SampleMask"));
727 args->push_back(gl_SampleMask->deepCopy());
728
729 TIntermAggregate *callSampleMaskWriteFunc =
730 TIntermAggregate::CreateFunctionCall(*sampleMaskWriteFunc, args);
731 TIntermBlock *callBlock = new TIntermBlock;
732 callBlock->appendStatement(callSampleMaskWriteFunc);
733
734 TIntermSymbol *coverageMaskEnabled = new TIntermSymbol(coverageMaskEnabledVar);
735 TIntermIfElse *ifCall = new TIntermIfElse(coverageMaskEnabled, callBlock, nullptr);
736
737 return RunAtTheEndOfShader(this, &root, ifCall, symbolTable);
738}
739
740ANGLE_NO_DISCARD bool TranslatorMetalDirect::insertRasterizationDiscardLogic(TIntermBlock &root)
741{
742 TSymbolTable *symbolTable = &getSymbolTable();
743
744 TType *boolType = new TType(EbtBool);
745 boolType->setQualifier(EvqConst);
746 TVariable *discardEnabledVar =
747 new TVariable(symbolTable, constant_names::kRasterizationDiscardEnabled.rawName(), boolType,
748 constant_names::kRasterizationDiscardEnabled.symbolType());
749
750 const TVariable *position = BuiltInVariable::gl_Position();
751 TIntermSymbol *positionRef = new TIntermSymbol(position);
752
753 // Create vec4(-3, -3, -3, 1):
754 auto vec4Type = new TType(EbtFloat, 4);
755 TIntermSequence *vec4Args = new TIntermSequence();
756 vec4Args->push_back(CreateFloatNode(-3.0f));
757 vec4Args->push_back(CreateFloatNode(-3.0f));
758 vec4Args->push_back(CreateFloatNode(-3.0f));
759 vec4Args->push_back(CreateFloatNode(1.0f));
760 TIntermAggregate *constVarConstructor =
761 TIntermAggregate::CreateConstructor(*vec4Type, vec4Args);
762
763 // Create the assignment "gl_Position = vec4(-3, -3, -3, 1)"
764 TIntermBinary *assignment =
765 new TIntermBinary(TOperator::EOpAssign, positionRef->deepCopy(), constVarConstructor);
766
767 TIntermBlock *discardBlock = new TIntermBlock;
768 discardBlock->appendStatement(assignment);
769
770 TIntermSymbol *discardEnabled = new TIntermSymbol(discardEnabledVar);
771 TIntermIfElse *ifCall = new TIntermIfElse(discardEnabled, discardBlock, nullptr);
772
773 return RunAtTheEndOfShader(this, &root, ifCall, symbolTable);
774}
775
776// Metal needs to inverse the depth if depthRange is is reverse order, i.e. depth near > depth far
777// This is achieved by multiply the depth value with scale value stored in
778// driver uniform's depthRange.reserved
779bool TranslatorMetalDirect::transformDepthBeforeCorrection(TIntermBlock &root,
780 const TVariable &driverUniforms)
781{
782 const TVariable *position = BuiltInVariable::gl_Position();
783 TIntermSymbol *positionRef = new TIntermSymbol(position);
784
785 TVector<int> swizzleOffsetZ = {2};
786 TIntermSwizzle *positionZ = new TIntermSwizzle(positionRef, swizzleOffsetZ);
787
788 TIntermBinary *viewportZScale = GetDriverUniformDepthRangeReservedFieldRef(driverUniforms);
789
790 // Create the expression "gl_Position.z * depthRange.reserved".
791 TIntermBinary *zScale = new TIntermBinary(EOpMul, positionZ->deepCopy(), viewportZScale);
792
793 // Create the assignment "gl_Position.z = gl_Position.z * depthRange.reserved"
794 TIntermTyped *positionZLHS = positionZ->deepCopy();
795 TIntermBinary *assignment = new TIntermBinary(TOperator::EOpAssign, positionZLHS, zScale);
796
797 return RunAtTheEndOfShader(this, &root, assignment, &getSymbolTable());
798}

800void TranslatorMetalDirect::createAdditionalGraphicsDriverUniformFields(
801 std::vector<TField *> &fieldsOut)
802{
803 // Add coverage mask to driver uniform. Metal doesn't have built-in GL_SAMPLE_COVERAGE_VALUE
804 // equivalent functionality, needs to emulate it using fragment shader's [[sample_mask]] output
805 // value.
806 TField *coverageMaskField = new TField(new TType(EbtUInt), kCoverageMaskField.rawName(),
807 kNoSourceLoc, kCoverageMaskField.symbolType());
808 fieldsOut.push_back(coverageMaskField);
809
810 if (mEmulatedInstanceID)
811 {
812 TField *emuInstanceIDField = new TField(new TType(EbtInt), kEmuInstanceIDField.rawName(),
813 kNoSourceLoc, kEmuInstanceIDField.symbolType());
814 fieldsOut.push_back(emuInstanceIDField);
815 }
816}
817
818TIntermSwizzle *TranslatorMetalDirect::getDriverUniformNegFlipYRef(
819 const TVariable &driverUniforms) const
820{
821 // Create a swizzle to "negFlipXY.y"
822 TIntermBinary *negFlipXY = CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kNegFlipXY);
823 TVector<int> swizzleOffsetY = {1};
824 TIntermSwizzle *negFlipY = new TIntermSwizzle(negFlipXY, swizzleOffsetY);
825 return negFlipY;
826}

913static inline MetalShaderType metalShaderTypeFromGLSL(sh::GLenum shaderType)
914{
915 switch (shaderType)
916 {
917 case GL_VERTEX_SHADER:
918 return MetalShaderType::Vertex;
919 case GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
920 return MetalShaderType::Fragment;
921 case GL_COMPUTE_SHADER:
922 ASSERT(0 && "compute shaders not currently supported");
923 return MetalShaderType::Compute;
924 default:
925 ASSERT(0 && "Invalid shader type.");
926 return MetalShaderType::None;
927 }
928}
929
930bool TranslatorMetalDirect::translateImpl(TIntermBlock &root, ShCompileOptions compileOptions)
931{
932 TSymbolTable &symbolTable = getSymbolTable();
933 IdGen idGen;
934 ProgramPreludeConfig ppc(metalShaderTypeFromGLSL(getShaderType()));
935
936 if (!WrapMain(*this, idGen, root))
937 {
938 return false;
939 }
940
941 TInfoSinkBase &sink = getInfoSink().obj;
942#if 0
943 if (getShaderType() == GL_VERTEX_SHADER)
944 {
945 if (!ShaderBuiltinsWorkaround(this, &root, &symbolTable, compileOptions))
946 {
947 return false;
948 }
949 }
950#endif
951
952 // Strip any inactive variables from the program.
953 if (!RemoveInactiveInterfaceVariables(this, &root, getAttributes(), getInputVaryings(),
954 getOutputVariables(), getUniforms(),
955 getInterfaceBlocks()))
956 {
957 return false;
958 }
959
960 // Write out default uniforms into a uniform block assigned to a specific set/binding.
961 int defaultUniformCount = 0;
962 int aggregateTypesUsedForUniforms = 0;
963 int atomicCounterCount = 0;
964 for (const auto &uniform : getUniforms())
965 {
966 if (!uniform.isBuiltIn() && uniform.active && !gl::IsOpaqueType(uniform.type))
967 {
968 ++defaultUniformCount;
969 }
970
971 if (uniform.isStruct() || uniform.isArrayOfArrays())
972 {
973 ++aggregateTypesUsedForUniforms;
974 }
975
976 if (uniform.active && gl::IsAtomicCounterType(uniform.type))
977 {
978 ++atomicCounterCount;
979 }
980 }
981
982 if (aggregateTypesUsedForUniforms > 0)
983 {
984 if (!NameEmbeddedStructUniformsMetal(this, &root, &symbolTable))
985 {
986 return false;
987 }
988
989 bool rewriteStructSamplersResult;
990 int removedUniformsCount;
991
992 if (compileOptions & SH_USE_OLD_REWRITE_STRUCT_SAMPLERS)
993 {
994 rewriteStructSamplersResult =
995 RewriteStructSamplersOld(this, &root, &symbolTable, &removedUniformsCount);
996 }
997 else
998 {
999 rewriteStructSamplersResult =
1000 RewriteStructSamplers(this, &root, &symbolTable, &removedUniformsCount);
1001 }
1002
1003 if (!rewriteStructSamplersResult)
1004 {
1005 return false;
1006 }
1007 defaultUniformCount -= removedUniformsCount;
1008
1009#if 0
1010 // We must declare the struct types before using them.
1011 DeclareStructTypesTraverser structTypesTraverser(outputMSL);
1012 root->traverse(&structTypesTraverser);
1013 if (!structTypesTraverser.updateTree(this, root))
1014 {
1015 return false;
1016 }
1017#endif
1018 }
1019
1020 if (compileOptions & SH_EMULATE_SEAMFUL_CUBE_MAP_SAMPLING)
1021 {
1022 if (!RewriteCubeMapSamplersAs2DArray(this, &root, &symbolTable,
1023 getShaderType() == GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER))
1024 {
1025 return false;
1026 }
1027 }
1028
1029#if 0
1030 // Write default uniform block
1031 if (defaultUniformCount > 0)
1032 {
1033 gl::ShaderType shaderType = gl::FromGLenum<gl::ShaderType>(getShaderType());
1034 sink << "\nstruct " << kDefaultUniformNames[shaderType] << "\n{\n";
1035 DeclareDefaultUniformsTraverser defaultTraverser(&sink, getHashFunction(), &getNameMap());
1036 root->traverse(&defaultTraverser);
1037 if (!defaultTraverser.updateTree(this, root))
1038 {
1039 return false;
1040 }
1041
1042 sink << "};\n";
1043 }
1044#endif
1045
1046 const TVariable &driverUniforms = *[&]() {
1047 if (getShaderType() == GL_COMPUTE_SHADER)
1048 {
1049 return AddComputeDriverUniformsToShader(root, symbolTable);
1050 }
1051 else
1052 {
1053 std::vector<TField *> additionalFields;
1054 createAdditionalGraphicsDriverUniformFields(additionalFields);
1055 return AddGraphicsDriverUniformsToShader(root, symbolTable, additionalFields);
1056 }
1057 }();
1058
1059 if (atomicCounterCount > 0)
1060 {
1061 // ANGLEUniforms.acbBufferOffsets
1062 const TIntermBinary *acbBufferOffsets =
1063 CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kAcbBufferOffsets);
1064
1065 if (!RewriteAtomicCounters(this, &root, &symbolTable, acbBufferOffsets))
1066 {
1067 return false;
1068 }
1069 }
1070 else if (getShaderVersion() >= 310)
1071 {
1072 // Vulkan doesn't support Atomic Storage as a Storage Class, but we've seen
1073 // cases where builtins are using it even with no active atomic counters.
1074 // This pass simply removes those builtins in that scenario.
1075 if (!RemoveAtomicCounterBuiltins(this, &root))
1076 {
1077 return false;
1078 }
1079 }
1080
1081 if (getShaderType() != GL_COMPUTE_SHADER)
1082 {
1083 if (!ReplaceGLDepthRangeWithDriverUniform(*this, root, driverUniforms))
1084 {
1085 return false;
1086 }
1087
1088#if 0
1089 // Add specialization constant declarations. The default value of the specialization
1090 // constant is irrelevant, as it will be set when creating the pipeline.
1091 if (compileOptions & SH_ADD_BRESENHAM_LINE_RASTER_EMULATION)
1092 {
1093 sink << "layout(constant_id="
1094 << static_cast<uint32_t>(vk::SpecializationConstantId::LineRasterEmulation)
1095 << ") const bool " << kLineRasterEmulationSpecConstVarName << " = false;\n\n";
1096 }
1097#endif
1098 }
1099
1100 {
1101 bool usesInstanceId = false;
1102 bool usesVertexId = false;
1103 for (const ShaderVariable &var : mAttributes)
1104 {
1105 if (var.isBuiltIn())
1106 {
1107 if (var.name == "gl_InstanceID")
1108 {
1109 usesInstanceId = true;
1110 }
1111 if (var.name == "gl_VertexID")
1112 {
1113 usesVertexId = true;
1114 }
1115 }
1116 }
1117
1118 if (usesInstanceId)
1119 {
1120 root.insertChildNodes(
1121 FindMainIndex(&root),
1122 TIntermSequence{new TIntermDeclaration{BuiltInVariable::gl_InstanceID()}});
1123 }
1124 if (usesVertexId)
1125 {
1126 if (!ReplaceVariable(this, &root, BuiltInVariable::gl_VertexID(),
1127 &kgl_VertexIDMetal))
1128 {
1129 return false;
1130 }
1131 DeclareRightBeforeMain(root, kgl_VertexIDMetal);
1132 }
1133 }
1134 SymbolEnv symbolEnv(*this, root);
1135 // Declare gl_FragColor and glFragData as webgl_FragColor and webgl_FragData
1136 // if it's core profile shaders and they are used.
1137 if (getShaderType() == GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER)
1138 {
1139 bool usesPointCoord = false;
1140 bool usesFragCoord = false;
1141 bool usesFrontFacing = false;
1142 for (const ShaderVariable &inputVarying : mInputVaryings)
1143 {
1144 if (inputVarying.isBuiltIn())
1145 {
1146 if (inputVarying.name == "gl_PointCoord")
1147 {
1148 usesPointCoord = true;
1149 }
1150 else if (inputVarying.name == "gl_FragCoord")
1151 {
1152 usesFragCoord = true;
1153 }
1154 else if (inputVarying.name == "gl_FrontFacing")
1155 {
1156 usesFrontFacing = true;
1157 }
1158 }
1159 }
1160
1161 bool usesFragColor = false;
1162 bool usesFragData = false;
1163 bool usesFragDepth = false;
1164 bool usesFragDepthEXT = false;
1165 for (const ShaderVariable &outputVarying : mOutputVariables)
1166 {
1167 if (outputVarying.isBuiltIn())
1168 {
1169 if (outputVarying.name == "gl_FragColor")
1170 {
1171 usesFragColor = true;
1172 }
1173 else if (outputVarying.name == "gl_FragData")
1174 {
1175 usesFragData = true;
1176 }
1177 else if (outputVarying.name == "gl_FragDepth")
1178 {
1179 usesFragDepth = true;
1180 }
1181 else if (outputVarying.name == "gl_FragDepthEXT")
1182 {
1183 usesFragDepthEXT = true;
1184 }
1185 }
1186 }
1187
1188 if (usesFragColor && usesFragData)
1189 {
1190 return false;
1191 }
1192
1193 if (usesFragColor)
1194 {
1195 AddFragColorDeclaration(root, symbolTable);
1196 }
1197
1198 if (usesFragData)
1199 {
1200 if (!AddFragDataDeclaration(*this, root))
1201 {
1202 return false;
1203 }
1204 }
1205 if (usesFragDepth)
1206 {
1207 AddFragDepthDeclaration(root, symbolTable);
1208 }
1209 else if(usesFragDepthEXT)
1210 {
1211 AddFragDepthEXTDeclaration(*this, root, symbolTable);
1212 }
1213
1214 // Always add sample_mask. It will be guarded by a function constant decided at runtime.
1215 bool usesSampleMask = true;
1216 if (usesSampleMask)
1217 {
1218 AddSampleMaskDeclaration(root, symbolTable);
1219 }
1220
1221#if 0
1222 if (compileOptions & SH_ADD_BRESENHAM_LINE_RASTER_EMULATION)
1223 {
1224 if (!AddBresenhamEmulationFS(this, compileOptions, sink, root, &symbolTable,
1225 driverUniforms, usesFragCoord))
1226 {
1227 return false;
1228 }
1229 }
1230#endif
1231
1232 if (usesPointCoord)
1233 {
1234 TIntermBinary &flipXY = *CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kNegFlipXY);
1235 TIntermConstantUnion &pivot = *CreateFloatNode(0.5f);
1236 TIntermBinary *fragRotation = nullptr;
1237 if (!RotateAndFlipBuiltinVariable(*this, root, *GetMainSequence(root), flipXY,
1238 *BuiltInVariable::gl_PointCoord(),
1239 kFlippedPointCoordName, pivot, fragRotation))
1240 {
1241 return false;
1242 }
1243 DeclareRightBeforeMain(root, *BuiltInVariable::gl_PointCoord());
1244 }
1245
1246 if (usesFragCoord)
1247 {
1248 if (!InsertFragCoordCorrection(*this, compileOptions, root, *GetMainSequence(root),
1249 driverUniforms))
1250 {
1251 return false;
1252 }
1253 DeclareRightBeforeMain(root, *BuiltInVariable::gl_FragCoord());
1254 }
1255
1256 {
1257 TIntermBinary *flipXY = CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kFlipXY);
1258 TIntermBinary *fragRotation = nullptr;
1259 if (!RewriteDfdy(this, &root, symbolTable, getShaderVersion(), flipXY, fragRotation))
1260 {
1261 return false;
1262 }
1263 }
1264
1265 if (usesFrontFacing)
1266 {
1267 DeclareRightBeforeMain(root, *BuiltInVariable::gl_FrontFacing());
1268 }
1269
1270 EmitEarlyFragmentTestsGLSL(*this, sink);
1271 }
1272 else if (getShaderType() == GL_VERTEX_SHADER)
1273 {
1274 DeclareRightBeforeMain(root, *BuiltInVariable::gl_Position());
1275
1276 if (FindSymbolNode(&root, BuiltInVariable::gl_PointSize()->name()))
1277 {
1278 DeclareRightBeforeMain(root, *BuiltInVariable::gl_PointSize());
1279 }
1280
1281 if (FindSymbolNode(&root, BuiltInVariable::gl_VertexIndex()->name()))
1282 {
1283 if (!ReplaceVariable(this, &root, BuiltInVariable::gl_VertexIndex(),
1284 &kgl_VertexIDMetal))
1285 {
1286 return false;
1287 }
1288 DeclareRightBeforeMain(root, kgl_VertexIDMetal);
1289 }
1290#if 0
1291 if (compileOptions & SH_ADD_BRESENHAM_LINE_RASTER_EMULATION)
1292 {
1293 if (!AddBresenhamEmulationVS(this, root, &symbolTable, driverUniforms))
1294 {
1295 return false;
1296 }
1297 }
1298#endif
1299 // Append a macro for transform feedback substitution prior to modifying depth.
1300 if (!AppendVertexShaderTransformFeedbackOutputToMain(*this, symbolEnv, root))
1301 {
1302 return false;
1303 }
1304
1305 // Search for the gl_ClipDistance usage, if its used, we need to do some replacements.
1306 bool useClipDistance = false;
1307 for (const ShaderVariable &outputVarying : mOutputVaryings)
1308 {
1309 if (outputVarying.name == "gl_ClipDistance")
1310 {
1311 useClipDistance = true;
1312 break;
1313 }
1314 }
1315
1316 if (useClipDistance && !ReplaceClipDistanceAssignments(
1317 this, &root, &symbolTable,
1318 CreateDriverUniformRef(driverUniforms, kClipDistancesEnabled)))
1319 {
1320 return false;
1321 }
1322
1323 if (!transformDepthBeforeCorrection(root, driverUniforms))
1324 {
1325 return false;
1326 }
1327
1328 if (!AppendVertexShaderDepthCorrectionToMain(*this, root))
1329 {
1330 return false;
1331 }
1332 }
1333 else if (getShaderType() == GL_GEOMETRY_SHADER)
1334 {
1335 WriteGeometryShaderLayoutQualifiers(
1336 sink, getGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType(), getGeometryShaderInvocations(),
1337 getGeometryShaderOutputPrimitiveType(), getGeometryShaderMaxVertices());
1338 }
1339 else
1340 {
1341 ASSERT(getShaderType() == GL_COMPUTE_SHADER);
1342 EmitWorkGroupSizeGLSL(*this, sink);
1343 }
1344
1345 if (getShaderType() == GL_VERTEX_SHADER)
1346 {
1347 auto &negFlipY = *getDriverUniformNegFlipYRef(driverUniforms);
1348
1349 if (mEmulatedInstanceID)
1350 {
1351 if (!EmulateInstanceID(*this, root, driverUniforms))
1352 {
1353 return false;
1354 }
1355 }
1356
1357 if (!AppendVertexShaderPositionYCorrectionToMain(*this, root, negFlipY))
1358 {
1359 return false;
1360 }
1361
1362 if (!insertRasterizationDiscardLogic(root))
1363 {
1364 return false;
1365 }
1366 }
1367 else if (getShaderType() == GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER)
1368 {
1369 if (!insertSampleMaskWritingLogic(root, driverUniforms))
1370 {
1371 return false;
1372 }
1373 }
1374
1375
1376
1377 if (!validateAST(&root))
1378 {
1379 return false;
1380 }
1381
1382 if (!RewriteKeywords(*this, root, idGen, GetMslKeywords()))
1383 {
1384 return false;
1385 }
1386
1387 if (!ReduceInterfaceBlocks(*this, root, idGen))
1388 {
1389 return false;
1390 }
1391
1392 if (!SeparateCompoundStructDeclarations(*this, idGen, root))
1393 {
1394 return false;
1395 }
1396 // This is the largest size required to pass all the tests in
1397 // (dEQP-GLES3.functional.shaders.large_constant_arrays)
1398 // This value could in principle be smaller.
1399 const size_t hoistThresholdSize = 256;
1400 if (!HoistConstants(*this, root, idGen, hoistThresholdSize))
1401 {
1402 return false;
1403 }
1404
1405 Invariants invariants;
1406 if (!RewriteGlobalQualifierDecls(*this, root, invariants))
1407 {
1408 return false;
1409 }
1410 const bool needsExplicitBoolCasts = (compileOptions & SH_ADD_EXPLICIT_BOOL_CASTS) != 0;
1411 if (!AddExplicitTypeCasts(*this, root, symbolEnv, needsExplicitBoolCasts))
1412 {
1413 return false;
1414 }
1415
1416 PipelineStructs pipelineStructs;
1417 if (!RewritePipelines(*this, root, idGen, driverUniforms, symbolEnv, invariants,
1418 pipelineStructs))
1419 {
1420 return false;
1421 }
1422 if (getShaderType() == GL_VERTEX_SHADER)
1423 {
1424 if (!IntroduceVertexAndInstanceIndex(*this, root))
1425 {
1426 return false;
1427 }
1428 }
1429 if (!SeparateCompoundExpressions(*this, symbolEnv, idGen, root))
1430 {
1431 return false;
1432 }
1433
1434 if (!RewriteCaseDeclarations(*this, root))
1435 {
1436 return false;
1437 }
1438
1439 if (!RewriteUnaddressableReferences(*this, root, symbolEnv))
1440 {
1441 return false;
1442 }
1443
1444 if (!RewriteOutArgs(*this, root, symbolEnv))
1445 {
1446 return false;
1447 }
1448 if(!FixTypeConstructors(*this, symbolEnv, root))
1449 {
1450 return false;
1451 }
1452 if (!ToposortStructs(*this, symbolEnv, root, ppc))
1453 {
1454 return false;
1455 }
1456 if (!EmitMetal(*this, root, idGen, pipelineStructs, invariants, symbolEnv, ppc))
1457 {
1458 return false;
1459 }
1460
1461 ASSERT(validateAST(&root));
1462
1463 return true;
1464}
1465
1466bool TranslatorMetalDirect::translate(TIntermBlock *root,
1467 ShCompileOptions compileOptions,
1468 PerformanceDiagnostics *perfDiagnostics)
1469{
1470 if (!root)
1471 {
1472 return false;
1473 }
1474
1475 TInfoSinkBase &sink = getInfoSink().obj;
1476
1477 if ((compileOptions & SH_REWRITE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRICES) != 0 && getShaderVersion() >= 300)
1478 {
1479 // "Make sure every uniform buffer variable has a name. The following transformation relies on this."
1480 // This pass was removed in e196bc85ac2dda0e9f6664cfc2eca0029e33d2d1, but currently finding it still necessary for MSL.
1481 // TODO(jcunningham): Look into removing the NameNamelessUniformBuffers and fixing the root cause in RewriteRowMajorMatrices
1482 if (!NameNamelessUniformBuffers(this, root, &getSymbolTable()))
1483 {
1484 return false;
1485 }
1486 if (!RewriteRowMajorMatrices(this, root, &getSymbolTable()))
1487 {
1488 return false;
1489 }
1490 }
1491
1492 bool precisionEmulation = false;
1493 if (!emulatePrecisionIfNeeded(root, sink, &precisionEmulation, SH_GLSL_VULKAN_OUTPUT))
1494 {
1495 return false;
1496 }
1497
1498#if 0
1499 bool enablePrecision = ((compileOptions & SH_IGNORE_PRECISION_QUALIFIERS) == 0);
1500
1501 TOutputMSL outputMSL(sink, getArrayIndexClampingStrategy(), getHashFunction(), getNameMap(),
1502 &getSymbolTable(), getShaderType(), getShaderVersion(), getOutputType(),
1503 precisionEmulation, enablePrecision, compileOptions);
1504#endif
1505
1506 if (!translateImpl(*root, compileOptions))
1507 {
1508 return false;
1509 }
1510
1511#if 0
1512 // Write translated shader.
1513 root->traverse(outputMSL);
1514#endif
1515
1516 return true;
1517}
1518bool TranslatorMetalDirect::shouldFlattenPragmaStdglInvariantAll()
1519{
1520 // Not neccesary for MSL transformation.
1521 return false;
1522}
